			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>SNAP = SUPPLEMENTAL Nutrition Assistance Program. It&#8217;s meant as a supplement to &#8212; not for paying for all &#8212; foods purchases. So all this talk of &#8220;I can&#8217;t live off $3.50 a day&#8221; nonsense needs to stop. You cannot live entirely off it because you are not meant to. I have never and likely will never be on food stamps so you can call me naive if you want, but take the program for what it&#8217;s mean to be &#8211; a temporary supplement to your existing income in order to purchase food. </p>
<p>To singlequeergrrl, as a taxpayer, it is absolutely my business whether or not they purchase booze. It is people like me that pays for these programs. Therefore, for some idiot to abuse it by selling SNAP benefits for 50 cents on the dollar so they can buy alcohol or cigarettes is fraud and misappropriation of my tax dollars.</p>
