	<li id="comment-129287">
		<div  class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 comment-wrap" >
			<div class="comment-avatar"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/6e2396ce05bf049218c226f9d570ab9b?s=45&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-45 photo' height='45' width='45' /></div>
			<div class="author-comment">
				<cite class="fn">Bill Wallace</cite> 				<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://aattp.org/panera-bread-ceo-learns-poverty-firsthand-week-poverty/#comment-129287">	September 27, 2013 at 10:40 pm</a></div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
			</div>
			<div class="clear"></div>
			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>I notice that I have gotten some flak over my benefit amount assumptions. I do understand that everyone&#8217;s benefit is different. My intention was to demonstrate that the amount that they assumed that you would need for food as a full benefit was adequate to feed a family with good nutritious meals every day. I wanted to show that it was not necessary to live on hamburger and non nutritious foods using their assumed food budget. I have used this food budget for a very long time and do understand how to make it work.</p>
<p>SNAP stands for Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program and was intended to supplement the food budget not replace it. Thus as your income rose, they expected you to devote some of your earnings towards your food budget. Now given the modern situation with restrictions on income eligibility, this is no longer a reasonable assumption. I certainly do believe that the current income restrictions are inappropriate and hurt a lot of people. When costs for everything goes up and wages or assistance in coping with price increases don&#8217;t, people&#8217;s situations become worse.</p>
<p>We do need to work on this by both fixing the laws and securing a living wage. Certainly raising the minimum wage would help, but even at $11.00/ hr, an adequate SNAP benefit is needed  The current effort to destroy SNAP is a very bad idea..</p>
			</div>
			<div class="reply"><a class='comment-reply-link' href='/panera-bread-ceo-learns-poverty-firsthand-week-poverty/?replytocom=129287#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-129287", "129287", "respond", "16180")'>Reply</a></div><!-- .reply -->
		</div><!-- #comment-##  -->

