			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>The problem with it these days comes from exactly that acronym. Remember back in the day, it was just &#8220;food stamps.&#8221; As in, something you use to buy food. The minute they changed it to &#8220;SUPPLEMENTAL nutrition,&#8221; they were sending a subtle message that &#8220;Yeah, here&#8217;s a little extra.&#8221; Back before they TEApublicans rose to power, you could get by on food stamps. But between them cutting funding, and the benefits amount not keeping up with inflation, now it is truly &#8220;supplemental.&#8221; At this rate, in five years it&#8217;ll be called &#8220;Barely Anti-Starvation Rationing Dispensary.&#8221; Or &#8220;BAStaRD,&#8221; for short.</p>
