			<div class="author-comment">
				<cite class="fn">MARK</cite> 				<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://aattp.org/panera-bread-ceo-learns-poverty-firsthand-week-poverty/#comment-129140">	September 27, 2013 at 10:02 am</a></div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
			</div>
			<div class="clear"></div>
			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>Try living on a SNAP program budget without any aid from the Government.<br />
My wife and I live it every day. All of our money goes to our household bills (which most of the SNAP programs enlistees get this assistance as well through Hud, energy assistance)<br />
And the entire extra goes to major medical bills that were due to a brain hemorrhage. Sure, I have good insurance; it paid 80%, but my out of pocket<br />
costs were over 35,000 dollars. No Government help here folks cuz I am in the lower middle class and don’t “qualify” for squat. So, we had to stop internet service, cancel cell phones, and all of the perks that  The SNAP programs participate enjoy by enrolling in all of the other programs, i.e.: Hud, free Obama phones, 250 fun money because they are under stress.<br />
Sorry if I show no sympathy to your cause, but I see these people every day with better shoes, smart phones, buying junk food with their SNAP cards, all boxed food in their shopping carts because they don’t want to prepare food, and worst of all, never looking for employment,<br />
While I on the other hand, spend my one day off from work at the library researching how to maintain a garden in the winter months and using their computer to bash you bleeding heart liberals for crying that the SNAP program needs more funding. BS…it needs to be better managed.</p>
			</div>
