	<li id="comment-129092">
		<div  class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 comment-wrap" >
			<div class="comment-avatar"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/6e2396ce05bf049218c226f9d570ab9b?s=45&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-45 photo' height='45' width='45' /></div>
			<div class="author-comment">
				<cite class="fn">Bill Wallace</cite> 				<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://aattp.org/panera-bread-ceo-learns-poverty-firsthand-week-poverty/#comment-129092">	September 27, 2013 at 3:29 am</a></div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
			</div>
			<div class="clear"></div>
			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>To all of you naysayers that say you can&#8217;t eat balanced meals on budget</p>
<p>Tonight&#8217;s dinner was oven baked parmesan breaded pork chops with sautéed green beans and herbed rice. Desert was fresh peach cobbler.<br />
I purchased a 4 pack of pork chops for $3.29 / lb on clearance (regularly $5.99 / lb) for $3.75. Since I had one left over, I planned to use it for school lunch paninis. Meat cost = $ 2.80.<br />
I used $0.10 bread crumbs from $1.00 loaf of bread, toasted and blended, 1 egg for $0.11 from eggs on sale for 18 for $1.98, $0.35 for Parmesan cheese from a shaker bottle and flour for $.10. Salt, pepper and dried herbs for $0.04 Breading cost = $0.75 for all four.<br />
Frozen green beans $0.99 / lb with about $0.25 fresh garlic, olive oil and soy sauce. Veggie cost = $1.25<br />
Rice with butter and herbs about $0.50<br />
Peach cobbler Peaches were on sale for $0.99 / lb I used $2.00 of peaches and biscuit dough recipe for $1.50 because of the butter to make 12 servings. Cost per serving = $0.30<br />
Beverages; two 12 oz milks from a $1.87 sale gallon = $0.36 plus 1 ice coffee. Cost = $0.50<br />
Total cost for this meal was $ 6.70 or $ 2.23 per serving</p>
<p>This means that I had $ 7.77 left over from my $ 14.00 average SNAP allotment for 3 people. That&#8217;s enough for a nice lunch and breakfast.</p>
<p>Tomorrow&#8217;s dinner: Salmon and spinach wrapped in filo with roast potatoes. Since salmon was on clearance for $4.99 / lb, I think that my meal cost will be around $ 8.00 or $2.70 per serving with $6.00 left over for breakfast and lunch. </p>
<p>You can eat real fresh food on this budget. Full price hamburger at $4.99 / lb plus a box of hamburger helper for $1.50 = $6.50. My meal cost the same amount. So tell me again why you are eating hamburger helper and nasty hot dogs.</p>
			</div>
