				<p>Bill tell us how you made the purchases. What I mean by this was what stores, how did you get to the store? How much of it was lower cost because you were able to purchase more in bulk?  See part of the problem people have on SNAP is that the stores they have access to arent the mega stores that sell at lower cost. They cant take advantage of purchasing in larger quantities because they never have enough up front.  They cant purchase a bottle of olive oil that lasts a long time and end up paying $0.25 per serving because they dont have the upfront money to do so.</p>
