	<li id="comment-129573">
		<div  class="comment even depth-4 comment-wrap" >
			<div class="comment-avatar"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/6e2396ce05bf049218c226f9d570ab9b?s=45&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-45 photo' height='45' width='45' /></div>
			<div class="author-comment">
				<cite class="fn">Bill Wallace</cite> 				<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://aattp.org/panera-bread-ceo-learns-poverty-firsthand-week-poverty/#comment-129573">	September 28, 2013 at 9:16 pm</a></div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
			</div>
			<div class="clear"></div>
			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>It is true that we are spoiled by our cooking facilities in America, but many cultures around the world can cook healthy meals with very limited equipment. You have to adapt your menu.<br />
I do have a normal fridge / freezer combo and a 3 burner stove.</p>
<p>When I was young, my father did not work summers and we traveled all over US and Canada every summer. We lived in a tent and cooked on a 2 burner Coleman stove all summer long. We always had full balanced meals just like we had at home. we were not rich and always stayed in no fee unimproved forest service camp grounds. We had a frugal lifestyle year round too..The point is that you do not need a fancy kitchen to cook good food</p>
<p>My situation is not as bad as many peoples, but I struggle to keep my family in housing and fed. My wife, Trina, developed ovarian cancer in 2006 and I provided full time hospice care for her for 3.5 years because she was very ill. As a result, we lost everything that we had worked for including our company and our house because her family looted it while I was caring for her. My company had provided fully paid health insurance for everyone (including their families) along with good wages. Now I am too old or over qualified for anyone to hire me. I work as a consulting chemist and restore vintage motorcycles to support my family. But work is scarce, so some months are good and some months, i have very little income.</p>
<p>But I have fed my family for many years on a low budget. I am lucky because I have a good family and a place to live.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="reply"><a class='comment-reply-link' href='/panera-bread-ceo-learns-poverty-firsthand-week-poverty/?replytocom=129573#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-129573", "129573", "respond", "16180")'>Reply</a></div><!-- .reply -->
