				<p>There are many small stores that will tally your cigarettes and beer up and ring you up for the equivalent in food sales, usually rounding up the price a few dollars to make a tidy little profit. Some will even do the same for cash, charging anywhere from $1 to $2 per $10 of &#8220;food&#8221; charged. If there is a way to make money off something you can be sure people will find a way.</p>
