			</div>
			<div class="clear"></div>
			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>It is a card, and you can sell them. On the street food stamps go for 50/100. That means you sit in the car while someone takes your food stamp card inside, you give them your PIN number, and they spend $100 of your food stamps, and they, in return, give you $50. If you only want to sell $30 on your food stamps, you will receive $15. Weather it is $15 cash, or $15 in pills or drugs, that is how it is done on the &#8220;streets&#8221;. Also, at gas stations that manually enter a price, ussually locally owned BP&#8217;s or AMERISTOP&#8217;s or SUNOCO, they can enter your cigarettes as food, because they are just entering a price&#8230; and they usually charge an extra fee for doing the favor.</p>
			</div>
