				<p>to add to that, a lot of people aren&#8217;t poor because they had bad things happen to them. Yes, some. I am not denying the GM plants closing and people loosing thousands of jobs&#8230; but, A lot of people are poor because they were never taught how to do good. You work full time for minimum wage and are struggling to pay your rent, electric, gas for work, car insurance, the LAST thing on your agenda is learning how to make home made bread. You get off work at 5, cook a quick meal, do kids home work, take baths, go to bed, repeat. Not everyone was taught growing up, how to cook or plan meals. Nobody learns in school how to balance a check book, how to spend wisely, how to cook wholesome meals, how to shop for car insurance. If your parents weren&#8217;t taught, you won&#8217;t be taught. Unless you have enough time on your hands, you will never learn.</p>
