	<li id="comment-129050">
		<div  class="comment even depth-2 comment-wrap" >
			<div class="comment-avatar"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/a5153cfe19d642357f878926d6111cfe?s=45&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-45 photo' height='45' width='45' /></div>
			<div class="author-comment">
				<cite class="fn"><a href='http://gravatar.com/student4now' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>student4now</a></cite> 				<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://aattp.org/panera-bread-ceo-learns-poverty-firsthand-week-poverty/#comment-129050">	September 26, 2013 at 10:01 pm</a></div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
			</div>
			<div class="clear"></div>
			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>You have $13.50 for a day&#8217;s worth of food for you, your spouse and your child &#8212; you decide that you&#8217;re going to cook everything because it&#8217;s healthier and you&#8217;re tired of the comments and glares for buying soda and TV dinners,  but your cupboards are bare. You need flour, sugar, milk, salt, pepper, oil, margarine, bread, milk and eggs &#8212; you are now past your $13.50 &#8211;and you&#8217;ve not bought anything to EAT  much less enough to prepare anything of value &#8212; so you put it back and you get soda because $0.89 for a 2 liter is less expensive than a gallon of milk at $3; you get white bread because it&#8217;s almost half the cost of wheat; you get a package of cookies because your kids deserve a treat now and then and it would cost almost $10 to make them from scratch. You get macaroni and cheese with hot dogs for dinner and once again you&#8217;re up to your budget for the day and  you know that the nutrion is severely lacking &#8212; but your children will not feel hungry and be able to sleep &#8212; and you feel like a heel  &#8212; and society is going to do everything to make you feel worse &#8212; and instead of understanding that it&#8217;s DAMN hard &#8212; they will point to the soda and junk instead of the hard work it is to be poor.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="reply"><a class='comment-reply-link' href='/panera-bread-ceo-learns-poverty-firsthand-week-poverty/?replytocom=129050#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-129050", "129050", "respond", "16180")'>Reply</a></div><!-- .reply -->
		</div><!-- #comment-##  -->

