	<li id="comment-129074">
		<div  class="comment odd alt depth-2 comment-wrap" >
			<div class="comment-avatar"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/431e9c74767a74391d1a11a29ec0fd7c?s=45&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-45 photo' height='45' width='45' /></div>
			<div class="author-comment">
				<cite class="fn">Been there, Done that</cite> 				<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://aattp.org/panera-bread-ceo-learns-poverty-firsthand-week-poverty/#comment-129074">	September 27, 2013 at 12:42 am</a></div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
			</div>
			<div class="clear"></div>
			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>I had to go on SNAP for my daughter and myself after her mother left us.  I worked full time but did not make enough on a single income to support the two of us.  Do you know what my &#8216;benefits&#8217; amounted to?  $57/month.  After paying bills and incidentals to take care of the two of us for the month I was lucky to have $50 for food so that extra $57 made one hell of a difference.  Did I but TV dinners, hot dogs, mac &amp; cheese and whatever else was cheap? You bet your ass I did, because I had to make the food last for as many meals as I could.  When off brand TV dinners are $1 each and an 8 pack of Hot Dogs are $1 each that&#8217;s dinner for a month for both of us with a couple bucks to buy cheap snacks like pre baked cookies and a bag of cheeto&#8217;s.  The fact is you do not know the circumstances of the people you are seeing in line buying pop, chips and cookies with their food.  For all you know they could be living in a group home and need to buy food they can store.  </p>
<p>My experience with the program led me to start my own charity group that focuses on making the lives of children better.  We donate time, money, and during the holidays gifts to needy families who have to choose between buying food or paying the bills (and holidays adds the burden of choosing to NOT but presents for the children).  Instead of knocking these people get to know them and their story.  Work with local groups to help change the system so they don&#8217;t have to rely on the system to feed their children.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="reply"><a class='comment-reply-link' href='/panera-bread-ceo-learns-poverty-firsthand-week-poverty/?replytocom=129074#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-129074", "129074", "respond", "16180")'>Reply</a></div><!-- .reply -->
		</div><!-- #comment-##  -->

	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li id="comment-129088">
		<div  class="comment even depth-2 comment-wrap" >
			<div class="comment-avatar"><img alt='' src='http://i1.wp.com/graph.facebook.com/100000520284899/picture?q=type%3Dlarge%26_md5%3Dd93b8e4708cc1b67772703d18de782f2&#038;resize=45%2C45' class='avatar avatar-45 photo' height='45' width='45' /></div>
