			</div>
			<div class="clear"></div>
			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>How wonderful that you can adopt the moral superiority to tell someone else how to live and raise their family. &#8220;Learn to cook&#8221;? That&#8217;s your solution? For all you know, that person in front of you in line may be working 2 or 3 jobs just to pay rent and utilities. How much time is left to cook? For all you know, a couple of kids might be looking forward to a glass of soda and an oh-so-extravagant Little Debbies cake once or twice a week for a treat that can make their humble lives seem a little more &#8220;normal&#8221;. Who has made you the arbiter of another&#8217;s life? If we eliminate that $4 &#8211; $14 a day food subsidy, what difference would it make in your life? None. But, the difference having that subsidy makes to a struggling family is the difference, literally, between life and death.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="reply"><a class='comment-reply-link' href='/panera-bread-ceo-learns-poverty-firsthand-week-poverty/?replytocom=129088#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-129088", "129088", "respond", "16180")'>Reply</a></div><!-- .reply -->
