				<p>I&#8217;m homeless (living in my car). I&#8217;m sitting in my car right now picking up wifi that is left on after closing at a cafe. I have no place to properly store food and cook it. So, what do I eat? Cheap fast food, canned food sometimes, and junk food. I can get a meal&#8217;s worth of calories in a soda, bag of chips and a donut for less than $3. Please tell me about a mean&#8217;s worth of calories of healthy food I can buy for $3.</p>
<p>I get $200/month EBT.. That&#8217;s $6.67/day! Can you feed me for an entire day on that amount?  I&#8217;d love to be enlightened on how to get by all month on that. I never can.</p>
