			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>Not that it makes any difference to you, but&#8230;. About 72 percent of SNAP recipients live in households with children; more than one-quarter live in households with seniors or people with disabilities.   Fraud and mis-payment amounts to 3.8% of SNAP payments, compared to 17% fraud and mis-payment to the IRS.  In fiscal year 2012, USDA’s retailer fraud investigations resulted in 342 convictions and $57.7 million in recoveries.  When cases of SNAP fraud are reported in the news, it is because the offenders have been caught, evidence that states and USDA are aggressively combating fraud.  In the lame example you posted, you apparently failed to note that the person committing the fraud was busted and jailed.  Every dollar of SNAP aid stimulates the economy by $1.78   It&#8217;s called the Multiplier Effect.   Don&#8217;t believe any of this..?  Look it up for yourself.  Fox News (?) is lying to you again.</p>
