			<div class="clear"></div>
			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>The only assurance that you need, is to know that people cannot use foodstamps to buy booze and cigs.  I&#8217;m not sure what you eat, but $300 or $400/mo does not go very far.  If you eat rice and beans, vegetables and fruit, you will spend more than that.  The point is that, yes, you can buy mac and cheese, and instant soups, but you will suffer in the future, and the  health care costs will outweigh the savings.  On top of that, 1 in 5 kids in this country go hungry at night.  Are they spending their money on booze and cigs too?</p>
			</div>
