			</div>
			<div class="clear"></div>
			<div class="comment-content">
									
				<p>So many in America are food insecure &#8211; myself included. I have a 14 year old son and nutrition is VITAL to his growth and development right now. I go into debt every month just from paying for food. I weigh 125 which is underweight for my 5&#8217;8 1/2 height because I sometimes don&#8217;t eat regularly myself to ensure HE has food. So on low energy I work my tail off, little sleep, improperly nourished and totally afraid of getting sick because I&#8217;m the only parent and bread winner in the family. Remember, you don&#8217;t want to pay for my healthcare, either. I also don&#8217;t have FS, even though I work for myself and my income fluctuates every month to the point I sometimes can&#8217;t even pay my rent in full, I make TOO MUCH MONEY to receive assistance. Get off your high horses!</p>
			</div>
